WEBVTT

00:00:15.375 --> 00:00:17.250
Ready? Let's open it.

00:00:28.583 --> 00:00:30.292
There's nothing in here...

00:00:31.667 --> 00:00:32.750
Hey, wait.

00:00:33.208 --> 00:00:35.958
I'll be okay. I'm not
going in too far...

00:00:35.958 --> 00:00:41.083
Besides, we need to at least see the boss,
or we won't know how to beat it.

00:00:41.083 --> 00:00:42.625
That's true, but...

00:01:16.500 --> 00:01:20.917
<i>The cowardly past that I'd acknowledged</i>

00:01:21.250 --> 00:01:26.708
<i>Still not understanding why,</i>

00:01:27.042 --> 00:01:37.583
<i>I stand behind myself, scared</i>
<i>Projecting reality onto today</i>

00:01:37.917 --> 00:01:42.917
<i>I've drawn so many skies</i>

00:01:43.250 --> 00:01:47.583
<i>This must be my fleeting heart</i>

00:01:47.917 --> 00:01:50.292
<i>Out of control</i>

00:01:50.625 --> 00:01:55.875
<i>In my dreams, this body soars so high</i>

00:01:56.292 --> 00:02:01.167
<i>And it can brush away any fears that cling to me</i>

00:02:01.500 --> 00:02:07.625
<i>Asleep inside me, these budding</i>
<i>feelings start to expand</i>

00:02:07.958 --> 00:02:11.583
<i>I realize this, weak as I am...</i>
<i>As long as I had you</i>

00:02:11.917 --> 00:02:16.875
<i>I could stay strong in this dark world</i>

00:02:17.208 --> 00:02:22.875
<i>My heart will dream a long dream forever</i>

00:02:23.792 --> 00:02:26.250
<i>I want to always be with you</i>

00:02:26.583 --> 00:02:31.917
<i>I'll give you everything I have...</i>

00:02:35.000 --> 00:02:39.042
"The Blue-Eyed Demon"

00:02:45.500 --> 00:02:47.417
That one's gonna be tough.

00:02:47.417 --> 00:02:48.958
Yeah...

00:02:48.958 --> 00:02:51.708
At a glance, it only
had one big sword,

00:02:51.708 --> 00:02:53.750
but I'm sure it has special attacks.

00:02:53.750 --> 00:02:58.208
We'll have to put tanks in the
front row and keep switching.

00:02:58.208 --> 00:03:01.042
I'd like to have around
10 shield users or so.

00:03:01.542 --> 00:03:03.208
Shield users, huh?

00:03:03.667 --> 00:03:04.708
Wh-What?

00:03:05.333 --> 00:03:07.458
You're hiding something, aren't you?

00:03:08.083 --> 00:03:09.583
What's this, all of a sudden?

00:03:09.583 --> 00:03:10.708
Well, it makes no sense.

00:03:11.542 --> 00:03:15.917
Normally, the biggest advantage of a
one-handed sword is using a shield.

00:03:15.917 --> 00:03:19.167
But I've never seen you with one.

00:03:19.875 --> 00:03:22.625
I don't use them because
they slow down my rapier.

00:03:23.125 --> 00:03:25.792
Some people don't because they
put style ahead of function, but...

00:03:27.792 --> 00:03:30.917
You don't seem to be using the sword
you commissioned from Liz either.

00:03:31.875 --> 00:03:33.167
How suspicious is that?

00:03:41.708 --> 00:03:42.917
Oh, well, never mind!

00:03:43.833 --> 00:03:46.375
After all, it's rude to pry
into people's skills.

00:03:48.292 --> 00:03:51.500
Anyway, it's gotten late,
but let's have lunch.

00:03:51.500 --> 00:03:52.500
What?

00:03:52.708 --> 00:03:54.375
D-Did you make it yourself?

00:03:54.958 --> 00:03:56.167
Yes.

00:03:56.167 --> 00:03:58.250
Take off your gloves
before you eat, okay?

00:03:58.250 --> 00:03:59.667
R-Right.

00:04:00.958 --> 00:04:02.375
Here you go!

00:04:08.708 --> 00:04:09.833
This is good!

00:04:11.625 --> 00:04:14.292
But how did you get this taste?

00:04:14.708 --> 00:04:17.250
That's the result of a year's
training and study.

00:04:18.083 --> 00:04:19.875
Aincrad has around
100 seasonings.

00:04:19.875 --> 00:04:21.875
To make it,

00:04:21.875 --> 00:04:26.875
I calculated all the parameters the
flavor-recreation engine uses.

00:04:26.875 --> 00:04:30.500
This was made with grogua seed,
shugra leaf and calim water.

00:04:32.167 --> 00:04:33.583
It's mayonnaise...

00:04:33.583 --> 00:04:37.583
This was made with abilba seed,
sag leaves, and ulafish bone.

00:04:40.333 --> 00:04:42.542
Th-This nostalgic taste...

00:04:43.958 --> 00:04:45.125
It's soy sauce!

00:04:48.167 --> 00:04:50.375
I made the sauce for the
sandwich with these.

00:04:50.375 --> 00:04:51.583
Wow.

00:04:51.583 --> 00:04:52.792
It's perfect!

00:04:52.792 --> 00:04:55.125
If you sold these, you'd make a fortune.

00:04:55.458 --> 00:04:57.167
W-Would I?

00:04:57.167 --> 00:05:00.000
N-No, you can't.

00:05:00.750 --> 00:05:02.167
Wh-Why?

00:05:03.125 --> 00:05:04.958
I wouldn't want to lose my share.

00:05:08.500 --> 00:05:10.500
You're so greedy...

00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:14.583
I'll make you another one
if I'm in the mood, all right?

00:05:26.792 --> 00:05:28.375
Hey, Kirito!

00:05:28.375 --> 00:05:29.500
It's been a while!

00:05:32.333 --> 00:05:34.542
So you're still alive, Klein?

00:05:34.542 --> 00:05:37.292
You're as surly as ever, huh?

00:05:37.292 --> 00:05:38.417
Wait...

00:05:38.417 --> 00:05:39.792
What's going on here?

00:05:39.792 --> 00:05:43.542
Why would a solo player
like you be with a girl?

00:05:45.250 --> 00:05:46.458
Um...

00:05:46.458 --> 00:05:50.708
I'm sure you've met during boss fights,
but I'll introduce you anyway.

00:05:50.708 --> 00:05:53.542
This is Klein, of the
Furin Kazan guild.

00:05:53.542 --> 00:05:56.750
And this is Asuna, of the
Knights of the Blood Oath.

00:05:58.917 --> 00:06:00.458
Hey, say something...

00:06:00.458 --> 00:06:01.875
You lagging?

00:06:05.375 --> 00:06:09.667
H-Hello, my name is K-Klein!
I'm 24, single, and looking for a girlfr--

00:06:14.125 --> 00:06:15.125
Leader!

00:06:22.292 --> 00:06:25.042
You're Asuna, aren't you?

00:06:28.292 --> 00:06:31.208
H-Hey, they're not a
bad bunch, okay?

00:06:31.833 --> 00:06:33.833
The leader's face aside.

00:06:35.792 --> 00:06:36.875
Hey!

00:06:37.708 --> 00:06:39.125
That's payback!

00:06:39.125 --> 00:06:40.208
K-Klein!

00:06:40.208 --> 00:06:42.917
What did you say about my face, man?

00:06:46.375 --> 00:06:48.167
What's going on, Kirito?

00:06:48.167 --> 00:06:50.000
Uh, well...

00:06:50.333 --> 00:06:51.500
Hello there.

00:06:51.500 --> 00:06:54.875
I'll be partying with him for a while.
Nice to meet you.

00:06:56.000 --> 00:06:57.583
Kirito! Why, you...

00:06:57.583 --> 00:06:59.208
Hey! Hold on a second...

00:07:01.458 --> 00:07:02.458
Kirito!

00:07:05.250 --> 00:07:06.917
Is that...

00:07:06.917 --> 00:07:08.292
the Army?

00:07:09.083 --> 00:07:13.375
That's the massive guild that runs the
first floor. What are they doing up here?

00:07:13.792 --> 00:07:17.375
Ever since they sustained heavy
damage clearing floor 25,

00:07:17.375 --> 00:07:20.042
they're more focused on strengthening
their guild than clearing levels...

00:07:20.042 --> 00:07:21.917
and haven't been going
to the front lines.

00:07:25.833 --> 00:07:27.208
At ease!

00:07:33.750 --> 00:07:37.875
I am Lieutenant Colonel Corvatz
of the Aincrad Liberation Army.

00:07:38.083 --> 00:07:40.208
Kirito. I'm solo.

00:07:40.500 --> 00:07:43.167
Have you cleared the area up ahead?

00:07:43.833 --> 00:07:44.958
Yes.

00:07:44.958 --> 00:07:47.333
We have a map leading
to the boss room.

00:07:48.958 --> 00:07:52.458
Then I'd like you to hand over
that map data to us.

00:07:53.708 --> 00:07:55.750
You're telling us to
hand it over for free?

00:07:55.750 --> 00:07:58.917
Do you know how much of a
pain in the ass mapping is?

00:07:59.250 --> 00:08:03.292
We share information
and resources equally

00:08:03.292 --> 00:08:05.458
with civilian players!

00:08:05.958 --> 00:08:08.208
And we maintain order in battle

00:08:08.208 --> 00:08:11.583
to liberate all players from this
world as quickly as possible!

00:08:12.625 --> 00:08:17.750
Therefore, you are duty-bound
to cooperate with us!

00:08:18.792 --> 00:08:19.583
Listen, you...

00:08:19.583 --> 00:08:20.875
You bastard...

00:08:20.875 --> 00:08:21.958
Back off.

00:08:21.958 --> 00:08:25.250
I was going to go public with this data
when we got back to town anyway.

00:08:25.542 --> 00:08:26.542
It's not a big deal.

00:08:26.542 --> 00:08:27.750
Hey, hey...

00:08:27.750 --> 00:08:29.875
You're being way too nice, Kirito.

00:08:30.375 --> 00:08:32.917
I have no desire to make
money off map data.

00:08:37.333 --> 00:08:38.750
Thank you for your cooperation.

00:08:41.375 --> 00:08:44.583
If you're planning to pick a fight with
the boss, I'd recommend against it.

00:08:45.125 --> 00:08:46.792
That is my decision to make.

00:08:48.667 --> 00:08:50.958
I just looked in the room.

00:08:50.958 --> 00:08:53.792
And you won't get anywhere with that
boss with your troops at half strength!

00:08:54.667 --> 00:08:57.167
Look at your comrades.
They're exhausted!

00:08:57.958 --> 00:09:02.250
My men aren't so weak as
to give in this easily!

00:09:02.875 --> 00:09:05.125
Come on, men!
On your feet now!

00:09:12.667 --> 00:09:15.708
Are those guys gonna be okay?

00:09:16.292 --> 00:09:20.917
I'm pretty sure they wouldn't be foolish
enough to rush the boss sight unseen.

00:09:22.083 --> 00:09:24.708
Still, let's at least go and
keep an eye on them.

00:09:30.625 --> 00:09:32.917
Now which one of us
is being too nice?

00:09:38.708 --> 00:09:42.083
Um, well, Asuna...

00:09:42.875 --> 00:09:44.750
You see...

00:09:45.083 --> 00:09:49.625
He's inarticulate, unsociable, and he's
an idiot who's addicted to combat...

00:09:50.083 --> 00:09:52.500
But take care of Kirito for me!

00:09:58.042 --> 00:09:59.042
Okay!

00:10:00.417 --> 00:10:01.958
You can count on me!

00:10:12.583 --> 00:10:15.375
The only thing ahead is
the boss room, right?

00:10:16.000 --> 00:10:19.500
Maybe they used an item to go back?

00:10:24.375 --> 00:10:25.250
Asuna!

00:10:25.250 --> 00:10:26.708
Right!

00:10:26.708 --> 00:10:27.708
Hey!

00:10:33.292 --> 00:10:34.292
Idiots.

00:10:38.000 --> 00:10:40.167
Hey, are you okay?

00:10:51.042 --> 00:10:52.167
What are you doing?

00:10:52.167 --> 00:10:53.667
Hurry up and use your
teleport crystals!

00:10:54.000 --> 00:10:55.000
It's no good!

00:10:55.000 --> 00:10:57.250
The c-crystals aren't working!

00:10:59.250 --> 00:11:02.583
There hasn't been a boss room
with a trap like this before.

00:11:05.500 --> 00:11:09.042
For the Liberation Army, there
is no such word as "retreat"!

00:11:09.042 --> 00:11:11.458
Fight! Fight!

00:11:11.458 --> 00:11:13.083
You fools...

00:11:13.083 --> 00:11:14.792
What's going on?

00:11:15.750 --> 00:11:18.042
They can't use teleportation
crystals in there.

00:11:18.042 --> 00:11:19.500
If we go in,

00:11:19.500 --> 00:11:21.625
we might be able to open up
an escape route, but...

00:11:22.292 --> 00:11:24.292
Isn't there something we can do?

00:11:30.917 --> 00:11:34.292
Everyone... Charge!

00:11:34.625 --> 00:11:35.625
Don't do it!

00:11:55.333 --> 00:11:56.792
Hey...

00:11:56.792 --> 00:11:57.792
Hang on!

00:12:06.792 --> 00:12:08.292
Impossible.

00:12:13.458 --> 00:12:14.667
No...

00:12:24.958 --> 00:12:26.458
No.

00:12:26.458 --> 00:12:29.375
I can't...

00:12:33.083 --> 00:12:35.250
No!

00:12:36.667 --> 00:12:37.667
Asuna!

00:12:39.250 --> 00:12:40.833
Oh, what the hell!

00:13:03.125 --> 00:13:04.167
Get back!

00:13:06.750 --> 00:13:08.083
You okay?

00:13:08.083 --> 00:13:09.250
Thanks.

00:13:24.750 --> 00:13:26.083
<i>At this rate...</i>

00:13:31.292 --> 00:13:33.167
Kirito!

00:13:39.417 --> 00:13:42.250
<i>I've got to use it then?</i>

00:13:42.250 --> 00:13:43.250
<i>But...</i>

00:14:02.375 --> 00:14:05.000
<i>Damn it, this is no time</i>
<i>to be indecisive!</i>

00:14:05.458 --> 00:14:07.083
Asuna, Klein...

00:14:07.083 --> 00:14:09.833
I need you to hold it
off for 10 seconds!

00:14:11.083 --> 00:14:12.333
Got it!

00:14:24.167 --> 00:14:25.250
Okay, ready!

00:14:27.417 --> 00:14:28.458
Switch!

00:14:53.375 --> 00:14:57.375
Starburst Stream!

00:15:04.458 --> 00:15:06.750
Wh-What is that skill?

00:15:07.958 --> 00:15:08.958
<i>Faster...</i>

00:15:18.667 --> 00:15:20.167
<i>Even faster!</i>

00:15:47.500 --> 00:15:48.958
Is it...

00:15:50.458 --> 00:15:51.583
...over?

00:16:19.125 --> 00:16:20.125
Kirito!

00:16:20.458 --> 00:16:21.750
Kirito!

00:16:31.583 --> 00:16:32.708
Ow...

00:16:39.833 --> 00:16:42.292
How long was I out?

00:16:42.833 --> 00:16:44.417
Just a few seconds.

00:16:45.333 --> 00:16:47.667
You idiot! Acting so recklessly...

00:16:50.083 --> 00:16:52.208
If you hold me too tightly,

00:16:52.208 --> 00:16:54.208
I'll lose my last few HP.

00:16:57.167 --> 00:16:59.958
Corvatz and two others died.

00:17:02.542 --> 00:17:07.042
We haven't lost anyone to a
boss fight since floor 67.

00:17:07.750 --> 00:17:10.708
Can you even call this a boss fight?

00:17:10.708 --> 00:17:12.875
Damn that idiot Corvatz!

00:17:13.875 --> 00:17:16.583
There's no point if you die.

00:17:22.292 --> 00:17:25.333
Anyway, what was that just now?

00:17:26.625 --> 00:17:28.292
Do I have to say?

00:17:28.833 --> 00:17:30.125
Of course!

00:17:30.125 --> 00:17:32.000
I've never seen anything
like that before.

00:17:33.833 --> 00:17:35.542
An extra skill.

00:17:36.167 --> 00:17:37.583
Dual-wielding.

00:17:38.792 --> 00:17:40.333
Wh-What are the prerequisites?

00:17:40.708 --> 00:17:43.042
If I knew, I'd have
shared it by now.

00:17:43.667 --> 00:17:46.750
It isn't on the information
broker's skill list.

00:17:46.750 --> 00:17:50.125
Meaning it's exclusive to you...
It's a unique skill!

00:17:50.625 --> 00:17:53.000
Way to be a stranger, Kirito!

00:17:53.000 --> 00:17:56.125
Keeping quiet about such
an amazing secret skill.

00:17:56.125 --> 00:17:56.333
"One-handed Sword"
"Dual-wielding"
"Thrown Sword"

00:17:56.333 --> 00:17:59.917
I was looking at my skill window

00:17:59.917 --> 00:18:03.333
about six months ago,
and I just found it there.

00:18:04.333 --> 00:18:07.833
But if people found out that
I had a skill like this...

00:18:07.833 --> 00:18:10.917
Yeah, since MMO gamers
are the jealous type...

00:18:10.917 --> 00:18:13.292
I'm too good a guy to care,

00:18:13.292 --> 00:18:16.292
but lots of people would
be really envious.

00:18:16.875 --> 00:18:17.875
Not to mention...

00:18:20.292 --> 00:18:25.458
Well, suffering builds character,
so soldier on, young man.

00:18:27.542 --> 00:18:29.250
Say whatever you want.

00:18:31.583 --> 00:18:34.792
We should trigger the warp gate...
Do you want to go?

00:18:34.792 --> 00:18:36.917
No, I'll leave it to you.

00:18:37.542 --> 00:18:39.542
I'm exhausted...

00:18:39.542 --> 00:18:40.583
Got it.

00:18:40.958 --> 00:18:42.500
Have a safe trip back.

00:18:46.125 --> 00:18:47.417
And well...

00:18:47.417 --> 00:18:48.750
Kirito...

00:18:49.917 --> 00:18:53.958
When you ran in to rescue
those Army guys...

00:18:54.958 --> 00:18:55.958
What?

00:18:56.625 --> 00:18:59.042
Well... you know...

00:18:59.875 --> 00:19:01.250
I was glad.

00:19:01.792 --> 00:19:03.792
That's all. See you around.

00:19:11.250 --> 00:19:12.500
Hey, Asuna?

00:19:13.542 --> 00:19:14.750
I was so scared...

00:19:15.333 --> 00:19:19.042
I didn't know what
I'd do if you died.

00:19:19.792 --> 00:19:21.458
What are you talking about?

00:19:21.458 --> 00:19:24.000
You're the one who jumped in first.

00:19:26.333 --> 00:19:29.083
I'm going to take a leave of
absence from the guild.

00:19:29.083 --> 00:19:31.583
A-And do what?

00:19:31.917 --> 00:19:34.542
I said I'd party up with you...

00:19:34.917 --> 00:19:36.000
Did you already forget?

00:19:40.000 --> 00:19:40.875
"Asuna invites you to join her party."

00:20:06.375 --> 00:20:07.375
All right.

00:20:17.125 --> 00:20:20.125
"October 19, 2024"       "Floor 50: Algade"

00:20:20.458 --> 00:20:24.042
"A blue demon that annihilated
a large Army squad."

00:20:24.667 --> 00:20:29.000
"And a fifty-hit combo from a
dual-wielder who took it out himself."

00:20:29.542 --> 00:20:32.583
They're making a really
big deal out of it.

00:20:34.375 --> 00:20:36.917
Could they have blown
it up any bigger?

00:20:36.917 --> 00:20:38.125
And because of that,

00:20:38.125 --> 00:20:40.542
tons of swordsmen and information
brokers came over this morning.

00:20:40.542 --> 00:20:43.292
So now I can't even
stay at my lodgings.

00:20:43.292 --> 00:20:46.417
Isn't that your own fault?

00:20:46.417 --> 00:20:50.333
You said it was just our secret,
and you let everyone in on it.

00:20:59.250 --> 00:21:01.583
What are we going to do, Kirito?

00:21:02.208 --> 00:21:04.250
We have a big problem!

00:21:04.750 --> 00:21:05.167
"October 19, 2024"       "Floor 55: Grandzam"

00:21:05.167 --> 00:21:08.208
"October 19, 2024"       "Floor 55: Grandzam"
Kirito, outside of boss fights,

00:21:08.208 --> 00:21:10.250
"October 19, 2024"       "Floor 55: Grandzam"
I believe we've never met.

00:21:10.917 --> 00:21:15.750
Actually, we spoke shortly
at a conference on floor 67,

00:21:16.250 --> 00:21:17.875
Guild Commander Heathcliff.

00:21:18.750 --> 00:21:21.083
That was a difficult battle, wasn't it?

00:21:21.625 --> 00:21:24.333
We nearly lost some people, too.

00:21:24.917 --> 00:21:29.458
We're called the top guild, but our numbers
are never more than barely sufficient.

00:21:29.458 --> 00:21:35.417
And yet, here you are now, trying to poach
one of our most important players.

00:21:36.208 --> 00:21:40.583
If she's that important, you
should pick a better bodyguard.

00:21:41.000 --> 00:21:44.875
I apologize for the trouble
you had with Kuradeel.

00:21:45.417 --> 00:21:50.500
But we cannot allow our vice
commander to leave just like that.

00:21:52.875 --> 00:21:54.167
Kirito,

00:21:54.167 --> 00:21:57.458
if you want her, then take her with
your blade, your dual blades.

00:21:57.708 --> 00:22:01.292
If you can defeat me in combat,
you may take Asuna.

00:22:01.625 --> 00:22:03.083
But if you lose,

00:22:03.958 --> 00:22:06.667
you will join the Knights
of the Blood Oath.

00:22:10.833 --> 00:22:11.833
Very well.

00:22:11.833 --> 00:22:14.917
If you'd rather settle this with
swords, that's fine with me.

00:22:14.917 --> 00:22:17.125
Let's settle it with a duel.

00:22:30.125 --> 00:22:41.583
<i>The tolling of the faraway bells</i>
<i>sounded a little lonely to me</i>

00:22:41.917 --> 00:22:53.458
<i>So I tried harder, one more time,</i>
<i>this time soaring higher, all the way up</i>

00:22:53.875 --> 00:22:59.417
<i>Neither this reality that just keeps repeating itself</i>

00:22:59.750 --> 00:23:05.208
<i>Nor all my wishes, as numerous as the stars</i>

00:23:05.625 --> 00:23:10.625
<i>Now that I've found the tomorrow</i>
<i>I should strive for</i>

00:23:10.958 --> 00:23:15.917
<i>None of them can overcome these feelings of mine</i>

00:23:16.250 --> 00:23:22.708
<i>A world without end, opening up before my eyes</i>

00:23:23.042 --> 00:23:26.667
<i>Even if it's no more than a dream</i>

00:23:27.250 --> 00:23:34.000
<i>Even if I'm still lost, deep in my heart, it is strong</i>

00:23:34.333 --> 00:23:39.792
<i>Echoing forever and ever</i>

00:23:40.125 --> 00:23:46.292
<i>Shining softly, ever so softly</i>

00:23:47.083 --> 00:23:53.195
Next Time: "Crimson Killing Intent."
